text: Franklin County is a county in the U.S. state of Ohio. As of 2020, the population was 1,323,807, making it the most populous county in Ohio. Its county seat is Columbus, the state capital and most populous city in Ohio. Franklin County is named after Benjamin Franklin, one of the founding fathers of the United States. ==References== Category:1803 establishments in Ohio Category:Ohio counties
